com.bixlabs.bkotlin

Class KOptional<T>

  • com.bixlabs.bkotlin.KOptional<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    KOptional.EMPTY, KOptional.Some

    public class KOptional<T>

    A container object which may or may not contain a non-null value. If a value is present, isPresent will return true and KOptional.get will return the value.

    Additional methods that depend on the presence or absence of a contained value are provided, such as orElse (return a default value if value not present) and ifPresent (execute a block of code if the value is present).

    This is a value-based class; use of identity-sensitive operations (including reference equality (==), identity hash code, or synchronization) on instances of class KOptional may have unpredictable results and should be avoided.

    See Also:
    KOptional.get, class KOptional

      • map

        public <U> KOptional<U> map(kotlin.jvm.functions.Function1<? super T,? extends U> mapper)

        If a value is present, apply the provided mapping function to it, and if the result is non-null, return an class KOptional describing the result. Otherwise return an empty class KOptional

        This method supports post-processing on optional values, without the need to explicitly check for a return status. For example, the following code traverses a stream of file names, selects one that has not yet been processed, and then opens that file, returning an class KOptional

        val fis = names.filter { name -> !isProcessedYet(name) }
               .findFirst()
               .map { name -> FileInputStream(name) }

        Here, findFirst returns an KOptional, and then map returns an KOptional for the desired file if one exists.

        Type Parameters:
        U - The type of the result of the mapping function
        Parameters:
        mapper - a mapping function to apply to the value, if present
        Returns:
        an class KOptional describing the result of applying a mapping function to the value of this class KOptional, if a value is present, otherwise an empty class KOptional
        Throws:
        - if the mapping function is null
        See Also:
        class KOptional, class KOptional, class KOptional
